WFM-IGP serves as the Secretariat for three programs including The Coalition for the  International Criminal Court (CICC), The International Coalition for the Responsibility to Protect (ICRtoP), and The International Democratic Governance Program (IDG). These are coalitions of non-governmental organizations working on the issues of international justice, advancement of the Responsibility to Protect Norm, and UN transparency and reform, respectively. &#xd;
&#xd;
WFM-IGP CICC’s global network includes a range of civil society organizations that work in coordination within the larger structure in a variety of ways. These 75 national and regional coalitions help local NGOs coordinate efforts at the national level, share best practices, and ensure broad support from civil society. CICC has six European Coalitions, which include: French Coalition for the ICC, Georgian Coalition for the ICC, Moldovan Coalition for the ICC, Swiss Coalition for the ICC, Turkish Coalition for the ICC, and UK Coalition for the ICC.  &#xd;
&#xd;
WFM-IGP is a formal participant in several civil society networks engaged in lobby and advocacy including the Post-2015 Women’s Coalition and the Human Rights and Democracy Network as well as formal government networks such as the Group of Friends of the ICC and RtoP at the UN, and the ICC Informal Ministerial network, which affords important access to key decisions makers. &#xd;
&#xd;
Additionally, WFM-IGP holds membership with the following: Case Matrix Network, CIVICUS: World Alliance for Citizen Participation, Conference of NGOs in Consultative Relationship with the UN, Gender Equality Architecture Reform Campaign, Global Action Against Mass Atrocity Crimes, Global Partnership for the Prevention of Armed Conflict, International Coalition for the Responsibility to Protect (ICRtoP), NGO Working Group on the Security Council, Security Council Report, United Nations Department of Public Information, United Nations Economic and Security Council, World Federation of United Nations Associations, Center for Teaching about the UN, Center for UN Reform Education, and the Global Institute for the Prevention of Aggression.   &#xd;
&#xd;
WFM-IGP also holds formal consultative status at the UN, Assembly of States Parties, ICC, European Union and other international institutions.

